ific case, you can simply merge dimensions 2 and 3 of your M2 matrix, do a matrix multiply, and then reshape the resulting tensor.\nr = torch.mm(M1, M2.view(a, -1)).view(n, b, c)", "body": "@dDua yes, there is. For your specific case, you can simply merge dimensions 2 and 3 of your M2 matrix, do a matrix multiply, and then reshape the resulting tensor.\r\n```python\r\nr = torch.mm(M1, M2.view(a, -1)).view(n, b, c)\r\n```"}